JOHANNESBURG - A 24-year-old man, who is a nurse at Damango Government Hospital in northern Ghana, has been arrested for allegedly raping a 28-year-old Italian national who came to the hospital seeking treatment for malaria, Ghana Web reported. Northern Regional Police command spokesperson ASP Yussif Tanko confirmed the alleged incident took place last Friday morning in a private ward of the hospital. READ: Militia commits mass rape in Central African Republic: MSF Due to her illness, the victim had struggled to climb back into bed after visiting the bathroom on the second day after being hospitalised. The perpetrator then allegedly offered to help her, sitting by her side before feeling her up and raping her with the victim too weak to resist. READ: Zim serial rapist requests hanging rather than jail The man has denied the allegations while the Northern Regional headquarters of the police Criminal Investigations Department has taken over investigations. African News Agency